{
  "texts": [
    "The problem is symmetric if for all, otherwise, it is asymmetric.",
    "The mTSP involves multiple salesmen departing from a depot to visit other cities before returning to the depot, with each city visited only once, optimizing the total cost.A subclass of sTSP, defined in a plane with Euclidean distance as the cost metric, is known as the euclidean symmetric traveling salesman problem.",
    "DL-based algorithms primarily target this subclass, which will be henceforth referred to simply as the TSP.Figure 1 represents a TSP instance with 50 nodes, denoted as TSP50.",
    "In the figure, blue nodes represent cities, gray lines denote paths connecting cities, and the red loop denotes the optimal solution.2.2 Challenge of solving TSP TSP poses significant computational challenges.",
    "Algorithms such as exhaustive search, branch and bound [29,30], and dynamic programming [31] suffice for small-scale instances."
  ]
}